"n.谬误，错误 【英】 n.谬误，错误(an error in reasoning ) 【考】 anachronism : chronology / fallacy : logic(年代错误是年代学中 的错误/谬误是逻辑学 中的错误)disabuse : fallacy / cure : disease(改正消除错误/治疗 消除疾病)反义词：valid argument(正确的论证 ); valid reasoning(正确的推 理) 【记】 fall(错误)+acy→谬 误 【同】 同根词：fallible(易 犯错误的) n. 谬误(建立在错误或无效推论上的声明或论据); 错误信仰 【记】fall错－谬误fallacy导致fall 【类】anachronism: chronology = fallacy: logic年代错误是年代学中的错误 = 谬误是逻辑学中的错误disabuse: fallacy = cure: disease 改正消除错误 = 治疗消除疾病 【反】valid argument(有效的论证); valid reasoning(有效的推理) 【记】fall 倒下，摔跟头→范错误；false 错误的 fallacy (n.)  late 15c., ""deception, false statement,"" from Latin fallacia ""deception,"" noun of quality from fallax (genitive fallacis) ""deceptive,"" from fallere ""deceive"" (see fail (v.)). Specific sense in logic dates from 1550s. An earlier form was fallace (c.1300), from Old French fallace."
